API docs by Redocly

Wsf Schedule API (1.0.0)

Download OpenAPI specification:

Wsf Schedule API - Washington State Department of Transportation APIs

active-seasons

Each ActiveSeasons item represents a scheduling period for Washington State Ferry routes. Each season defines the time period when specific schedules are active and available for passenger travel planning.

Returns multiple of ActiveSeasons for all scheduling periods.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/activeseasons

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getActiveSeasons } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getActiveSeasons,
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 2 total)

[
  • {
    • "ScheduleID": 193,
    • "ScheduleName": "Fall 2025",
    • "ScheduleSeason": 2,
    • "SchedulePDFUrl": "http://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/pdf/2025Fall.pdf",
    • "ScheduleStart": "2025-09-21T07:00:00.000Z",
    • "ScheduleEnd": "2025-12-27T08:00:00.000Z"
    },
  • // ... 1 more item
]

sailings

Sailing information represents individual ferry trips with departure and arrival times, vessel assignments, and route details for scheduled ferry services.

Returns all sailing data for the specified scheduled route ID.

path Parameters
SchedRouteID
required
number

Unique identifier for scheduled route, as an integer ID. E.g., '2401' for Anacortes/San Juan Islands route in Fall 2025, '2383' for Port Townsend/Coupeville route. Use GetScheduledRoutes to retrieve valid scheduled route IDs. Used to identify which scheduled route to retrieve sailings for.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/allsailings/{SchedRouteID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getSailingsBySchedRouteID } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getSailingsBySchedRouteID,
  params: {
    "SchedRouteID": 2401
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

]

Returns sailing data for the specified scheduled route ID.

path Parameters
SchedRouteID
required
number

Unique identifier for scheduled route, as an integer ID. E.g., '2401' for Anacortes/San Juan Islands route in Fall 2025, '2383' for Port Townsend/Coupeville route. Use GetScheduledRoutes to retrieve valid scheduled route IDs. Used to identify which scheduled route to retrieve sailings for.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/sailings/{SchedRouteID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getSailingsBySchedRouteID } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getSailingsBySchedRouteID,
  params: {
    "SchedRouteID": 2401
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

route-details

Each RouteDetails item represents a ferry route with complete service information. Each route includes departure and arrival terminals, sailing times, vessel assignments, and route-specific details for travel planning.

Returns single of RouteDetails for specified route.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (RouteDetailsByTripDateAndRouteIdInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve detailed route information, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter route by trip date availability.

RouteID
required
number (RouteDetailsByTripDateAndRouteIdInputRouteIDParam)

Unique identifier for route, as an integer ID. E.g., '9' for Anacortes/San Juan Islands route, '6' for Edmonds/Kingston route. Use GetRoutes to retrieve valid routes. Used to identify specific route for detailed information.

Responses

Production server

routes

Each Routes item represents a ferry path between terminals. Each route includes route identification, terminal connections, and route-specific scheduling information for travel planning.

Returns multiple of Routes for specified date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (RoutesByTripDateInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve routes, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter routes by trip date availability.

query Parameters
DepartingTerminalID
number (RoutesByTripDateInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to filter routes by origin terminal. Optional - if omitted, returns all routes for trip date.

ArrivingTerminalID
number (RoutesByTripDateInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '10' for Friday Harbor terminal, '13' for Lopez Island terminal. Use GetTerminalsAndMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals. Used to filter routes by destination terminal. Optional - if omitted, returns all routes for trip date.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/routes/{TripDate}

service-disruptions

Each ServiceDisruption item represents planned or unplanned interruptions to normal ferry service, including cancellations, delays, and route changes that affect passenger travel plans.

Returns multiple of ServiceDisruption for specified trip date.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (RoutesHavingServiceDisruptionsByTripDateInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve routes with service disruptions, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter disrupted routes by trip date.

Responses

Production server

schedules

Each Schedules item represents a complete sailing timetable for ferry routes. Each schedule includes departure times, arrival times, vessel assignments, and route-specific scheduling information for travel planning.

Returns single of Schedules for terminal pair.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (ScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIdsInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for schedule lookup, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter schedules by trip date.

DepartingTerminalID
required
number (ScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIdsInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '10' for Friday Harbor terminal. Use GetTerminalsAndMates to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for schedule lookup.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (ScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIdsInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '13' for Lopez Island terminal, '15' for Orcas Island terminal. Use GetTerminalsAndMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals. Used to identify destination terminal for schedule lookup.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/schedule/{TripDate}/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIds } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getScheduleByTripDateAndDepartingTerminalIdAndTerminalIds,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-05",
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

scheduled-routes

Scheduled routes represent the predefined ferry routes with their associated schedule identifiers, used for organizing and retrieving sailing schedules.

Returns all scheduled routes.

query Parameters
ScheduleID
number (ScheduledRoutesInputScheduleIDParam)

Unique identifier for schedule season, as an integer ID. E.g., '193' for Fall 2025 schedule. Use GetActiveSeasons to retrieve valid schedule IDs. Optional - if omitted, returns all scheduled routes across current and upcoming seasons. Used to filter scheduled routes by specific season.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/schedroutes

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getScheduledRoutes } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getScheduledRoutes,
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

Example of a successful response from the API (showing first item of 16 total)

[
  • {
    • "ScheduleID": 193,
    • "SchedRouteID": 2401,
    • "ContingencyOnly": false,
    • "RouteID": 9,
    • "RouteAbbrev": "ana-sj",
    • "Description": "Anacortes / San Juan Islands",
    • "SeasonalRouteNotes": "The Anacortes-San Juan Islands route will operate its regular schedule on Thanksgiving and Christmas.",
    • "RegionID": 1,
    • "ServiceDisruptions": [ ],
    • "ContingencyAdj": [ ]
    },
  • // ... 15 more items
]

Returns scheduled routes for the specified schedule ID.

path Parameters
ScheduleID
required
number (ScheduledRoutesByIdInputScheduleIDParam)

Unique identifier for schedule season, as an integer ID. E.g., '193' for Fall 2025 schedule. Use GetActiveSeasons to retrieve valid schedule IDs. Optional - if omitted, returns all scheduled routes across current and upcoming seasons. Used to filter scheduled routes by specific season.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/schedroutes/{ScheduleID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getScheduledRoutesById } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getScheduledRoutesById,
  params: {
    "ScheduleID": 193
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

schedule-today

Today's schedule provides current day sailing information for ferry routes, with options to show only remaining times for real-time schedule information.

Returns today's schedule for the specified terminal pair.

path Parameters
DepartingTerminalID
required
number (ScheduleTodayByTerminalsInputDepartingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminalsAndMates to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for today's schedule.

ArrivingTerminalID
required
number (ScheduleTodayByTerminalsInputArrivingTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for arriving terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '10' for Friday Harbor terminal, '13' for Lopez Island terminal. Use GetTerminalsAndMates to retrieve valid arriving terminals. Used to identify destination terminal for today's schedule.

OnlyRemainingTimes
required
boolean (ScheduleTodayByTerminalsInputOnlyRemainingTimesParam)

Filter flag controlling whether past departures are included, as a boolean. E.g., true to show only remaining departures today, false to include all departures including past ones. Used to filter schedule to only upcoming sailings when true.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/scheduletoday/{DepartingTerminalID}/{ArrivingTerminalID}/{OnlyRemainingTimes}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getScheduleTodayByTerminals } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getScheduleTodayByTerminals,
  params: {
    "DepartingTerminalID": 1,
    "ArrivingTerminalID": 10,
    "OnlyRemainingTimes": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

}

Returns today's schedule for the specified route.

path Parameters
RouteID
required
number (ScheduleTodayByRouteInputRouteIDParam)

Unique identifier for route, as an integer ID. E.g., '9' for Anacortes/San Juan Islands route, '6' for Edmonds/Kingston route. Use GetRoutes to retrieve valid routes. Used to identify route for today's schedule.

OnlyRemainingTimes
required
boolean (ScheduleTodayByRouteInputOnlyRemainingTimesParam)

Filter flag controlling whether past departures are included, as a boolean. E.g., true to show only remaining departures today, false to include all departures including past ones. Used to filter schedule to only upcoming sailings when true.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/scheduletoday/{RouteID}/{OnlyRemainingTimes}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getScheduleTodayByRoute } from 'ws-dottie';

const data = await fetchDottie({
  endpoint: getScheduleTodayByRoute,
  params: {
    "RouteID": 9,
    "OnlyRemainingTimes": false
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

Response samples

  • 200
Content type
application/json

schedule-terminal-mates

Each TerminalMate item represents terminals that can be used interchangeably or as alternatives for ferry departures and arrivals, providing flexibility in route planning.

Returns multiple of Terminal for specified trip date and terminal ID.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (TerminalMatesInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve terminal mates, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter terminal mates by trip date availability.

TerminalID
required
number (TerminalMatesInputTerminalIDParam)

Unique identifier for departing terminal, as an integer ID. E.g., '1' for Anacortes terminal, '3' for Bainbridge Island terminal. Use GetTerminals to retrieve valid departing terminals. Used to identify origin terminal for finding available destination terminals.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/terminalmates/{TripDate}/{TerminalID}

Request samples

  • JavaScript
import { fetchDottie, getTerminalMates } from 'ws-dottie';

  endpoint: getTerminalMates,
  params: {
    "TripDate": "2025-11-05",
    "TerminalID": 1
  },
  fetchMode: 'native',
  validate: true
});

console.log(data);

schedule-terminals

Terminals represent the ferry dock locations where passengers board and disembark, including terminal identification, location information, and service details.

Returns terminals and their mates for the specified trip date and route.

path Parameters
TripDate
required
string (TerminalsAndMatesByRouteInputTripDateParam)

Trip date for which to retrieve terminal combinations, as a date string in YYYY-MM-DD format. E.g., '2025-11-02' for November 2, 2025. Must be within valid date range from GetScheduleValidDateRange. Used to filter terminal combinations by trip date and route.

RouteID
required
number (TerminalsAndMatesByRouteInputRouteIDParam)

Unique identifier for route, as an integer ID. E.g., '9' for Anacortes/San Juan Islands route. Use GetRoutes to retrieve valid routes. Used to filter terminal combinations by specific route.

Responses

Production server

https://www.wsdot.wa.gov/ferries/api/schedule/rest/terminalsandmatesbyroute/{TripDate}/{RouteID}

time-adjustments

Time adjustments represent modifications to scheduled sailing times, including delays, early departures, and other timing changes that affect the published schedule.

Returns time adjustments for the specified scheduled route ID.

path Parameters
SchedRouteID
required
number (TimeAdjustmentsBySchedRouteInputSchedRouteIDParam)

Unique identifier for scheduled route, as an integer ID. E.g., '2383' for Port Townsend/Coupeville route in Fall 2025. Use GetScheduledRoutes to retrieve valid scheduled route IDs. Used to filter time adjustments by specific scheduled route.

Responses

Production server
